          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white m-0">Email</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500">Formal communication, longer messages</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
        Connect your property's email via SMTP/IMAP. Jack monitors the inbox, responds to guest queries, and can escalate complex issues to staff.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-2">
        <a href="/docs/configuration/email/" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">Setup guide →</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900/30 flex items-center justify-center">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M21 12a9 9 0 01-9 9m9-9a9 9 0 00-9-9m9 9H3m9 9a9 9 0 01-9-9m9 9c1.657 0 3-4.03 3-9s-1.343-9-3-9m0 18c-1.657 0-3-4.03-3-9s1.343-9 3-9m-9 9a9 9 0 019-9"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white m-0">Web Chat</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500">Embedded on your website</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
        Add a chat widget to your website. Visitors can ask questions before booking. No setup required—just embed the provided script.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="unified-inbox">Unified Inbox</h2>

  <p>
    All channels feed into a single inbox in the dashboard. Staff see:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>All conversations in one list</li>
    <li>Channel indicator for each conversation</li>
    <li>Guest profile and history across channels</li>
    <li>Real-time message updates</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    If a guest contacts you on WhatsApp then later emails, both conversations link to the same guest profile.
  </p>

  <h2 id="guest-identity">Guest Identity</h2>

  <p>
    Jack identifies guests by their contact information:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>WhatsApp/SMS</strong> — Phone number</li>
    <li><strong>Email</strong> — Email address</li>
    <li><strong>Web Chat</strong> — Session-based (can link to email if provided)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    When a guest's phone and email are known, Jack links their conversations across channels automatically.
  </p>

  <h2 id="channel-specific">Channel-Specific Features</h2>

  <h3>WhatsApp</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Template messages for notifications</li>
    <li>Quick reply buttons</li>
    <li>Image and document sharing</li>
    <li>Read receipts and delivery status</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>SMS</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>160 character limit handling (auto-splits long messages)</li>
    <li>MMS support for images</li>
    <li>Delivery receipts</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Email</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>HTML formatting</li>
    <li>Attachment support</li>
    <li>Thread grouping</li>
    <li>Reply detection</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Web Chat</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Customizable widget appearance</li>
    <li>Pre-chat form for guest info</li>
    <li>Typing indicators</li>
    <li>File uploads</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="costs">Channel Costs</h2>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg">
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
      <li class="flex justify-between">
        <span>WhatsApp Business API</span>
        <span class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">Free (first 1000 conversations/month)</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex justify-between">
        <span>Twilio SMS</span>
        <span class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">~$0.0075/message (US)</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex justify-between">
        <span>Email</span>
        <span class="text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">Free (your existing email)</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex justify-between">
        <span>Web Chat</span>
        <span class="text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">Free (included)</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="setup">Setup Guides</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="/docs/configuration/whatsapp/">WhatsApp Setup</a></li>
    <li><a href="/docs/configuration/sms/">SMS Setup</a></li>
    <li><a href="/docs/configuration/email/">Email Setup</a></li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
